================================================================================
DATA SOURCE ATTRIBUTIONS & LICENSES
================================================================================

This software processes data from multiple sources, each with their own
licensing terms:

1. OPENSTREETMAP DATA
   ├─ License: Open Database License (ODbL) v1.0
   ├─ Source: https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright
   ├─ Copyright: © OpenStreetMap contributors
   ├─ Usage: Road network data (ways, nodes, tags)
   └─ Attribution Required: "© OpenStreetMap contributors"

2. ELEVATION DATA SOURCES

   a) SRTM (Shuttle Radar Topography Mission)
      ├─ License: Public Domain
      ├─ Source: USGS / NASA
      ├─ Coverage: Global (-60° to +60° latitude)
      ├─ Resolution: 30m
      └─ No attribution required (public domain)

   b) ASTER GDEM (Advanced Spaceborne Thermal Emission and Reflection)
      ├─ License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
      ├─ Source: NASA/METI
      ├─ Coverage: Global (-83° to +83° latitude)
      ├─ Resolution: 30m
      └─ Attribution Required: "ASTER GDEM is a product of NASA and METI"

   c) AW3D30 (ALOS World 3D - 30m)
      ├─ License: Free for research & commercial use (terms apply)
      ├─ Source: JAXA (Japan Aerospace Exploration Agency)
      ├─ Coverage: Global
      ├─ Resolution: 30m
      ├─ Attribution Required: "Based on AW3D30 DSM dataset (© JAXA)"
      └─ Terms: https://www.eorc.jaxa.jp/ALOS/en/dataset/aw3d30/aw3d30_e.htm

   d) NED (National Elevation Dataset)
      ├─ License: Public Domain
      ├─ Source: USGS
      ├─ Coverage: United States
      ├─ Resolution: 10m (1/3 arc-second)
      └─ No attribution required (public domain)

   e) REMA (Reference Elevation Model of Antarctica)
      ├─ License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
      ├─ Source: Polar Geospatial Center
      ├─ Coverage: Antarctica
      ├─ Resolution: 8m
      ├─ Attribution Required: "REMA © Polar Geospatial Center"
      └─ Citation: Howat et al. 2019, doi:10.7910/DVN/SAIK8B

   f) ArcticDEM
      ├─ License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0)
      ├─ Source: Polar Geospatial Center
      ├─ Coverage: Arctic regions (>60°N)
      ├─ Resolution: 2m-32m
      ├─ Attribution Required: "ArcticDEM © Polar Geospatial Center"
      └─ Citation: Porter et al. 2018, doi:10.7910/DVN/OHHUKH

3. GEOGRAPHIC BOUNDARIES
   ├─ Source: Natural Earth Data & Geofabrik regional extracts
   ├─ License: Public Domain
   └─ No attribution required

================================================================================
FULL ATTRIBUTION EXAMPLE FOR GENERATED DATA
================================================================================

When publishing or using climb data generated by this software, use this
attribution template:

    "This climb data was generated using Steve Holl's Climb Analyzer
     (https://github.com/stevehollx/climb-analyzer) and made available through 
     https://github.com/stevehollx/global-road-and-trail-climbs.

     Data sources:
     - Road network data © OpenStreetMap contributors (ODbL)
     - Elevation data: [SRTM (NASA/USGS) | ASTER GDEM (NASA/METI) |
       AW3D30 (JAXA) | NED (USGS) | REMA/ArcticDEM (Polar Geospatial Center)]
       [Include only the datasets actually used for your region]"

