COMMERCIAL USE GUIDELINES
================================================================================

GENERATED CLIMB DATA (CC BY 4.0):
- ✓ Can be used in commercial applications (including paid iOS apps)
- ✓ Can be redistributed and sold
- ✓ MUST include attribution as specified above
- ✓ Cannot claim exclusive rights to the data

UNDERLYING DATA SOURCES:
- ✓ OpenStreetMap: Must include © OSM contributors attribution (ODbL terms)
- ✓ SRTM/NED: Public domain, no restrictions
- ✓ ASTER/REMA/ArcticDEM: Must include attribution (CC BY 4.0)
- ✓ AW3D30: Must include attribution and follow JAXA terms

================================================================================
DISCLAIMER
================================================================================

The elevation data and road network data are provided "as-is" without warranty.
The accuracy of climb metrics depends on the quality of the underlying data
sources (OpenStreetMap and elevation datasets). Users should verify critical
information independently.

Elevation data accuracy varies by region and dataset:
- SRTM: ±16m vertical accuracy (official specification)
- ASTER: ±17m vertical accuracy
- AW3D30: ±5m vertical accuracy
- NED: ±2.4m vertical accuracy (US only)
- REMA: ±1m vertical accuracy (Antarctica)
- ArcticDEM: ±2m vertical accuracy (Arctic)

OpenStreetMap data completeness and accuracy varies by region and community
contribution levels.

